messages.text: Fun fact…
Did you know that mistletoe is poisonous?
Only if you eat it.
May cause drowsiness and blurred vision if you do.
Are you planning something? Should I be scared?
Well, I am still miffed about that kiss.
I was drunk, Ava. You can’t hold it against me.
You kissed me and called me Ashley.
Way to totally crush the girl who’s been crushing on you forever.
Ashley and I had just broken up.
It doesn’t mean I was thinking of her.
Well, you certainly weren’t thinking of me.
To be completely honest, I don’t know what I was thinking…
But I can tell you that I’ve been thinking of you ever since.
Ava’s lips part as she stares at her phone’s screen.
She met Kyle during freshman orientation.
But back then, he was inseparable from his then girlfriend.
Even so, Ava hadn’t been able to stop herself from fantasizing that he was hers.
I don’t know what to say.
Then tell me you’re not plotting my death by mistletoe.
LOL. No, just researching for a stupid assignment.
About mistletoe?
Tis the season.
I need to find some mistletoe for the presentation portion.
That’s why I’m texting you.
It’s due tomorrow 🤦‍♀️
It’s usually found in the woods, high up in a tree.
And since you’re a woodsy kind of guy…
You want me to help you?
Yes, please. I need an A in this class.
If I agree, will you finally forgive me?
You’re already forgiven, Kyle.
Being called by your ex’s name sucked, but I’m over it.
And over me too?
Ava nibbles on her lower lip.
The truth is, she’s not over her crush on Kyle…
But she’s pretty sure he’s not over his ex, Ashley, either.
Just last week she saw them walking together on campus.
They weren’t holding hands, but they’d looked like a couple.
How about this? If you agree to help me, I’ll owe you.
Well, then. Can’t say no to that arrangement.
BUT I won’t be eating or drinking anything you offer me, just in case.
LOL. Are you free this afternoon?
I’m all yours 🙂
Ava seriously doubts that will ever be true.
Great.
I’ll pick you up at your apartment in a little bit.
I know where we can look.
Thanks. I knew you were the guy for the job.
As Ava gets ready for Kyle to come pick her up…
She gets a text from her friend, Trisha.
I have some scoop!
It’s about why Kyle and Ashley broke up.
Apparently Ashley has been talking.
And?
And KYLE was the one who broke up with Ashley!
She said it’s because he likes someone else.
Who?
She wasn’t sure.
But Ava…what if it’s YOU?
It’s not me.
But a little thrill runs through Ava.
You never know.
Well, we’re going out this afternoon.
What? You’ve been holding out on me!
It’s no big deal. Kyle is helping me find mistletoe for my presentation.
Ohhh. Sounds romantic!
Make sure you put that mistletoe to good use when you find it 😉
The last thing I need is to kiss Kyle and have him call me Ashley again.
LOL. Everyone makes mistakes. Forgive and forget.
It’s the season for all that stuff, you know.
Well, I’ll be keeping my lips to myself.
Unless Kyle catches you under the mistletoe…
It’s bad luck not to kiss if he does.
I’ve done my research and that’s not even true 🙅‍♀️
Haha. Let me know how it goes this afternoon!
There’ll be nothing to tell, but okay.
Someone knocks on Ava’s apartment door.
She opens it to Kyle and her heart leaps up into her throat.
Could he have broken up with Ashley because he liked her?
Ready?
Yep. Let’s go on a mistletoe hunt!
They head toward his truck and Kyle opens her door for her.
Then he climbs into the driver’s seat and they take off.
He gives her a sidelong glance
You know, I was hoping you’d call me.
Well, I just texted and it was only because I needed a favor.
I’m still glad.
I could never do this on my own.
For one, I don’t like climbing trees.
For two, I have no sense of direction.
Going into the woods on my own is a bad idea.
Kyle laughs. The sound rumbles through the truck and jolts Ava’s heart.
She takes in the sight of his full lips parted.
And she can’t help but remember the feeling of his lips pressed against hers.
After a short drive, Kyle pulls up to a patch of woods and cuts the engine.
This shouldn’t take long.
Ava follows beside him.
This is a little scary, walking through the woods.
Don’t worry. I’m here all the time.
For what?
Mainly for hiking. I like to daydream and take in the scenery…
He looks over at her.
While I kick myself for being such an idiot where you’re concerned.
I can’t argue with that.
But we’ve already gone over what happened.
And it’s okay. We’re cool.
It’s not okay, but I’m glad you’re still talking to me…
Even if you’re not kissing me anymore.
Ava looks away, her gaze moving up to the low hanging branches above them.
Mistletoe!
Look, it’s right there!
You sure?
I think so.
Can you climb up and see?
Kyle starts to climb the tree.
He gets pretty close to the branch with the mistletoe.
But when it can’t support his weight…
He breaks off the limb and watches it fall to the ground.
Then he climbs down and picks up the branch that fell.
Score!
He offers it to Ava.
But just before she grabs it…
He lifts his arm and dangles it over her head.
Looks like I caught you under the mistletoe.
Kiss me?
Ava looks up and then back at him.
That isn’t mistletoe.
It isn’t?
There are no berries. It’s just a sprig of leaves!
Now that’s embarrassing.
Ava steps closer, her gaze pinned to his.
But we can pretend.
I mean, if you want.
I have a great imagination.
As long as you know it’s me that you’re kissing.
Kyle says Ava’s name and it comes out like a hum.
There’s no one else that I’d rather be caught under the mistletoe with.
Ava tilts her head up towards Kyle’s.
His lips caress hers, with an invitingly soft pressure.
And there in the forest, palpable between them…
Is tiny, but powerful, dose of Christmas magic.
